[normal]              [bold] [bold]Career service[bold] 
[normal]The University of Manchester provides a career service to all students during 
[normal]their studies and for two years after they graduate. In 2011 the careers service won the 'Times Higher Education Award for Outstanding Support for Early Career Researchers' for their dedicated academic career website for PhD and research staff. Recently (F
[normal]ebruary 2013) the 
[normal]Head of Post Graduate Career Development offered advice to students about PhD applications and career prospects in academic field, at the 
[normal]Faculty wide WiSET event, 
