[normal]8[bold].[bold]              [bold] [bold]What role should the Government have [bold]in encouraging the retention of women in academic STEM careers?[bold]8.1 
[normal]              
[normal]The government must offer support and recognition for women who juggle academic commitments and family commitments. Better maternity leave support from funding bodies should be provided s
[normal]o that all the support does not have to come through the University
[normal]. W
[normal]omen need see that they can have a career break, return to work and go on to further their career. 
[normal]8.2 
[normal]              
[normal]It would also greatly help if there was better support for 
[normal]partners
[normal] in terms of l
[normal]eave so that a couple can jointly care for their child, without the woman missing out on key progression points in her career.
[normal] 
[normal]8.3 
[normal]              
[normal]Programmes such as Athena SWAN should be more heavily invested in by the Government as they make a considerable impact on the number of departments that work towards gender equality. 
[normal]August 2013
